name: 6-DTC
band_comment: 6-DTC means "Six Dans ton Cul" (Six in Your Ass)
The band's logo is actually the roman numerals for the band's name: VI (6), IV (4), II (2), V (5).
The band only released one demo: "Nekrofilie," the first ever demo on the Czech thrash/black metal scene. It has been re-released on the Inkubatörr compilation by Törr.
The band refers to themselves as "True Carpathian Black Metal".
Played their first gig at Kagurazaka Explosion on June 6, 1986 (6/6/6), and played their last at the Shinjuku Loft in October 1988.
